Regulatory Affairs Manager
Regulatory Affairs Manager
Location:  Singapore
Salary:  USD90000 - USD100000 per annum + benefits
The Regulatory Affairs Manager is responsible for 4 SEA countries regulatory affairs, in which the company is doing business through distributors. Therefore the RA manager will work closely with Distributors to ensure the product to be registered timely in relevant country, and complied with the local regulations/guidelines.
This role will highly involve in the country business strategy discussion, and regulatory strategy setting. This is key internal channel for communicating to Global Regulatory Affairs, and others cross functional teams, i.e. Marketing, supply chain, medical, supply sites, the regional RA team, as well as the project team members etc.
The company requires a solid knowledge in the area of RA within the South East Asia.
This is a permanent position is the Singapore office.
Please contact me for further details
